Most of the changes will at once commend themselves The editors have in general been conservative in regard to spelling, especially th'e new spelling of old Gallie names, feeling that much that is proposed of that kind as yet lacks certainty. They have added very full suggestions for parallel reading, and have spared no pains to enrich the study of this famous piece of literature.
